caption: This place should be shut down immediately. Management staff is incredibly rude while the establishment remains a total mess. The food is basically non edible and the smoothies are all watered down. I also heard from numerous sources that the employees are poorly treated. Just terrible.

I used to work here and let me tell you it is nasty. The food is all extra processed and the it is SO unsanitary especially when it comes to cross contamination. At the end of the night the trash would leave streaks in the kitchen and it would be barley cleaned and the fridges where the frozen food was was always warm and extremely dirty. This place sucks I wish I could give it negative stars

If I could do less than 1 star I would. This place is so awfully run, they should be on an episode of Undercover Boss. They are always short staffed which puts so much pressure on the workers when the line is out the door. The food is poorly made, probably due to poor management. One time I came in and the poor girl had to close the store because only one other kid was working with her and the line was out the door. Whoever runs this franchise should either find a new career path or step up to the plate and become a true leader of this business so the underpaid workers don’t get blamed for your lack of professionalism.

Honestly never too thrilled with my experience here. I have heard numerous threats coming from upper management towards employees. I think that in order for this store to be successful it must be fixed from the big name employees before people start blaming the people you see when you walk in.
This place is absolutely terrible. The food is disgusting and it is definitely not clean. Not sure how this place is still open and I really hope nobody ever comes here again
I ordered ahead, my order was ready by the time I got there. The owner I presume made sure I had the correct order, he was very nice. My order was made to my specifications
The store said close at 7:00 pm but they close at 6:00pm

Poor customer service at this location poorly made wraps smoothies are good one star for smoothies.. I will not visit this location again. I went to McD they got my money I ask to speak to manager she tells me she don't have time shes busy Wow... How did she make manager with that attitude. Downtown Tampa Location
I do find the food a little expensive for the amount but the smoothies are delicious
Google maps says that you close at 7. The sign on your door says you close at 7. So why are you closed when I come at 6:50? Your smoothies are good but your disorganization is unacceptable.

I have tried this location 3 times (the third being my last).  The location is run without any organization.  The staff do not appear to generally understand what is going on and are extremely rude (with the exception as one gentleman).  The kitchen staff randomly puts orders out on the counter without announcing what they are (the latest time they "lost" the tickets so they could not announce whose orders they were).  The ordering and preparation of food takes a comically long amount of time.  The last two times I have been in it has taken 20+ minutes for a smoothie to be prepared.  I have never given a 1 star review before, however after 3 failed tries, this location gets one.  Save your time and your money and go elsewhere.

I waited 45 min for my order which was a detox smoothie and a shrimp wrap. After waiting all that time I asked about it and they hadn't even made it yet. When I finally got it, I had to rush out and leave only to find out they gave me a chicken burrito with beans. Not what I had ordered. Also they were not able to print out receipts for most transactions. I want my money back! I'm completely disappointed. Wasted my money and time!

I just want to preface this with the fact that Ive been to this location before and the service is normally fine. But today i waited over 40 minutes for just a smoothie and I ordered online as I always do. There is NO reason a smoothie should take that long to wait. And I had to remind the staff about my smoothie twice before it was even put in the blender. Not to mention that it wasn’t a great smoothie today cuz they didn’t read my order properly.

Extremely rude when I asked for my money back since I noticed the place was very dirty. I kept communicating with Davion in a professional manner while he became with quick and rude with his response since my refund was reflecting cash and not a debit to my account . I verified on my account In it was credited back. That’s all no need to become so rude along with a female staff who was leaving with a cake in hand. They both seemed to act an a bully behavior. I will never be back in will only have negative feedback to my friends about this place.

The staff was okay and I loved the music but the cafe was empty, and the tables were all dirty while the staff ran in and out of the store. Also, are the owners aware that the cafe is being closed at 6:30pm? I wanted to take something to-go and was told no by the girl working, right at 6:30pm. I was told that a sign would be posted tomorrow saying that was the new time. Is this true?
Taylor did a great job putting my order together and making sure everything was in the bag. GIVE HER A RAISE!😄

Service was okay... not bad but not great. I’m only writing a review due to the fact that my food was made incorrectly on an online order. Going forward please be sure to double check that everything is made as requested. Some people have food allergies or dietary restrictions that prohibit them from consuming certain foods. If I request for something to not be included please be sure to make it as requested.

2 stars since the sandwich was not bad. Got a Bahama Mama and tasted like pure water. Switched to a Peanut Butter Cup and was even worse than the Bahama Mama. I recommend to not waste the money on this location. Overall, poor smoothie making skills.

The employees here are INSANELY nice. Best customer service by far. I only come to this location specifically for the employees. And of course the food and smoothies are incredible, i'm seriously here 3-4 times a week!!
THE BEST WORKERS !
Great area to get a healthy drink also good fast service all around perfect vibe
Kinda slow but great service

was told by jason who i’m assuming is the manager to come in for a free smoothie since they had messed it up the day prior. went in today and he wasn’t there so i still had to end up paying. the smoothie tasted gross and wasn’t blended fully. wasted my time, won’t be back to this location.
Smoothies are fricken mind blowing and cute little place very clean

The smoothies are great. You get a 20oz cup of healthy goodness, pair that with a sandwich/wrap/quesadilla and you got yourself a good meal. Personally, the chipotle chicken club is a hit anytime. Service was pretty fast, granted that this is downtown Tampa.
Friendly staff
Made a bonehead mistake on leaving my wallet at home. Had my check book but no checks accepted. Still the Manager T hooked up a shake for my son. Thank you sir. I truly appreciate it.
Place is ran by children
Loved this place. Was in town for a mini vacay and ended up hitting these guys every day and on the day I left twice in the same day

Disappointed once again. The person in the back making sandwiches with her mask beneath her chin is unacceptable. This is the second time CDC protocol has not been followed at this location. I will NOT be going back.

My coworker and I  ordered smoothies, a roll and a flatbread.  We are currently part of the public health response to COVID19 and busy with conference calls and other response activities.  I noticed my roll was the wrong order.  I called the store to let them know there was an error.  As soon as I verbalized our limitations and where we worked, Jason immediately corrected the order and offered to bring it down to us.  You have know idea how much I appreciate this since our next break wasn't until 5pm today.  Thank you again for the superior customer service and yummy food.
Paid extra for whey protein and the team member said she added to much ice, so she tossed half of what was made in the sink since it didn’t fit in my cup.

I’ve been to this location around three times ever since I moved down here for college. The only thing I can say is that, it’s better than the Tropical Smoothies back in South Florida. I’ve ordered a turkey bacon ranch sandwich 2/3 times I’ve came here, and it was pretty good! It was made nicely, had the right amount of everything, very filling. NOW THE SMOOTHIES. I’ve only ordered the Avocolada & Kiwi Quencher in total at this place, doesn’t take watered down + flavorful. My only problem is the amount that’s given. They don’t put enough ice in their smoothies to fill it up to the top, so I’m left paying more for what I actually got. It’s happened to me all times I’ve been there and I hope it gets better because that can be a small dealbreaker for me with this place.  Customer service is alright, no one really looks the happiest when they’re there. But I find that to be a pattern at all of the Tropical Smoothies I’ve been to in my lifetime. Could be better though.  The cleanliness was up to par with this restaurant; no trash on the floors, lobby was kept nice and neat with the chairs pushed in. The bathrooms were pretty clean too, nothing to outrageously complain about. When it comes to the size of a restaurant, it’s better to maintain cleaning when it’s smaller.  Overall, I would keep coming here. I just don’t like the portion amount of smoothie they actually give me.
5 people in the kitchen and one at the counter and took over 30 minutes to get a lunch meal.  Saw some people just walk out without their food!

I'm over this dump.  A young woman was at the cash register when I walked in to place my order, and she was just finishing with the customer in front of me.  She looked right at me, ignored me and walked back into the kitchen.  I finally had to ask one of the other kitchen staff members if someone would please wait on me so I could get back to work.  I'd suggest firing the staff and starting over, but this place seems to have a penchant for hiring people who cop a lot of attitude with paying customers.

February 9th 2020 12:56pm the cashier was very slow and when ordering I asked for no kale on my chicken Cesar wrap. It took her 8 minutes to try and figure out how to do it on the register and finally asked for help from a co-worker. Will not be eating here again.
We’ve stopped here many times at this location and love it. Super good food, fast and done well.
Good protein smoothies

My go-to place for lunch since it's one building over from. Food is great, and staff is very courteous. I particularly love the All American Wrap for a quick breakfast, the chicken bacon ranch flatbread,  for a satisfying lunch, and a muscle monster smoothie. Also online ordering is very easy. Highly recommend if you're in the downtown area

I stopped in this morning on my way to a conference. The gentleman there was quick and kind. The smoothie is delicious.
Great food!

My food order was not correct upon arrival but I spoke with Jason, the manager, and he made a fresh order and delivered it personally to my office.  This was my first time ordering from Tropical Smoothie Cafe and will be ordering again due to this outstanding service.  This was also the first time I had ever ordered from Tropical.  If I'm in the area, I will also stop in to grab a bite.  Food was great by the way.

This place was packed and that's expected since it's downtown and everyone was on lunch. It didn't take 2 minutes and I was in and out.  I parked in the "cabs only parking" space because there is never any parking downtown for one. And for 2, the parking isn't free. I parked for free but watched my car like a hawk for those 2 minutes. 😭 I wouldnt recommend anyone parking where I parked but sometimes you have to risk that chance.  I didn't get a parking ticket and the smoothie was good. Mango Magic smoothie are awesome.

Stopped for Smoithies after a fun day in Tampa.  My daughter ordered the Sunrise Sunset Smoothie. It is good, however,  I would reccomend light orange juice.  I ordered a Acai Berry Boost. I subbed yogurt for the banana, it's too over powering for the berries, and is was delicious.  The only size they have is huge. See picture  below. Next time we will share one. A good value price wise  and a very good smoothie to end our day out.

I asked if one of the employees could add some more bananas to it and they said they’d just remake it for me, no charge. I’d recommend this to anyone who likes smoothies, and if they make it wrong just ask them to remake it.

HORRIBLE customer service! I WAS a loyal customer to this location but today changed that! I typically order my lunch through the app and pick it up on my break... it’s typically ready and I don’t have to wait which is why I use the app. Today I did my same routine but when I got there to pick it up... it was NOT ready! The woman behind the counter thought it was funny and told me it wouldn’t be ready for another 10 minutes! On top of that her customer service was horrible. The women behind me went up to order and the cashier literally did not acknowledge her for 5 minutes. The cashier was on the phone and made the women wait there after finally saying it would be a minute. At this point the line is out the door! Why don’t they have more ppl working at LUNCH TIME!? I’m confused *rolls eyes*

I ordered two flat breads from this place on Uber eats,  service was fast but when i got the food  it was cold and honestly disgusting i ordered a chicken pesto and  it literally had two pieces of chicken bathed in pesto sauce and half a slice of tomato. the second flatbread was a chipotle chicken club, it had one strip of bacon and a bunch of cheese no chicken whatsoever i was very disappointed. I also ordered a cookie and the forgot it.

The smoothies and flat breads are great! I think this particular store is a bit understaffed, especially during the busy lunch hour. The staff is friendly, but there does not seem to be any sense of urgency to get orders out. Overall, I'm pleased with their customer service.
Friendly staff, good food and smoothie options, and its casual enough to take the kids with you to dine in the restaurant as well.

I love tropical smoothie! I really do. This location has a lack of customer service orientation. Nobody welcomes the customers. Nobody apologize, nobody gives feedback or ask questions. They look like robots and ask only if you need a receipt. I am not coming to eat in this location anymore because my order was wrong , and i had to ask 2 times for it to be fixed. I ordered a Baja Chicken and there was no sauce no avocado, and there were onions too , which i asked not to. So nobody apologized, nobody even asked or give feedback that they understood what i was asking for. They look they are not happy to work here. Somebody need to talk with them and to observe how they treat a customer. They don’t treat customers the way a customer needs to be treated.
4th Street has lousy staff but good product.

Only reason why I gave it two stars was for the smoothie. Everything else was horrible. I walked in to pick up an online order, there is a long line of people at the register, no one at it. Once I realized this - I asked if I could please have it without - they didn't make any effort to correct the order and I ended up throwing it away. Rob and his crew at Tropical Smoothie are fabulous! The food is always on time and consistently great tasting.  What's more, this past week I had to provide lunch for 14 shareholders.  I had arranged another caterer who let me down by not showing up, despite at least3 emails outlining and confirming date & time, etc.  So, with no time to spare I placed a call to Tropical Smoothie and spoke with Amanda.  I explained my predicament and in 20 minutes I had a well presented tray of assorted wraps, sandwiches, assorted chips and cookies!!!  Tropical Smoothie saved the day!
